</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ubaldoleafsway.showPublicProfile?language=EN>BaldoLeafsway</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.geocities.com/sando999/wolf.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(11/22/01 9:25:24 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.home.earthlink.net/~sando1000/bepic.jpg height=194 width=159></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: How to kill a 60 epic wizard</span><hr size=1> Sunbeam?  Fist of Karana?<br>
<br>
LOL, you dueling bluebies are funny :)<br>
<br>
On the non-carebear servers (The PvP Servers), everyone has MR 100+ and FR/CR 150-200.  Everyone has full Blue Diamond gear.  We dont care about 200 wis/int and +300 mana.  We care about resists.<br>
<br>
If you try and wind up on a wizard with chain Scorie, hes going to laugh at you while he uses lures to hump you.  If you cast Winged Death, hes going to dispel it off.  If you dispel his skin, he is going to re-apply it.<br>
<br>
(By the way, dots arent protected by the wiz epic shield or by any skin.  Dots chew under them. They have to take those off immeadiately. Which is nice :)<br>
<br>
The best way to kill a wizard who knows what hes doing and who has good resists, is let him spend mana on nukes (which is all he can do) and save your mana for heals.  Also dispel his skin off.<br>
<br>
The way you kill him is melee. >)<br>
<br>
Nothing is better than whacking a wizzie to death with the leafblower.  If you have played right, you will have enough mana to nuke him when he tries to gate.<br>
<br>
If he gets the drop on you and dispells you and gets ahead of your healing curve... forget it.  You will die.<br>
<br>
Respect the wizard.  They are arguably the most lethal and powerful PvPers.  A good druid with good gear should beat them in my oponion, but often times it comes down to the resist rolls.  It can be close.<br>
<br>
