<br>
Having played both Wizard (to very high level) and Druid (to moderately high level) I have a fair clue on this topic.<br>
<br>
I've beaten and been beaten by druids as my wizard.  My wizard has epic and magic/fire/cold resists of about 150 each.<br>
<br>
If the druid does not have similar resists, they will die, no matter how competent the druid, if the wizard has half a clue.<br>
If you cant reliably resist sunstrike/ISOS (or even draughts) you are toast, simple as that.<br>
<br>
If the only option available to the wizard is lures, then a well played druid will defeat him, as Balbo said, by using melee and self healing.<br>
<br>
And for those who's precious druids are uber wizard killa's, you forget how useless you are against any mob over level 60.  Remember classes have strengths in some areas and weak in others.  Druids are no exception, neither are wizards.<br>
<br>
I love my wizard, I love my druid too - they are actually remarkably different classes.<br>
<br>
Cheers<br>
Calina <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ustormhaven.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Stormhaven</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>FAQ/Index Moderator</span><br> <font color=#333399>(11/27/01 1:34:39 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://web2.airmail.net/naomi/amalgam/forum/stormhaven.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: How to kill a 60 epic wizard</span><hr size=1> I found the easiest way to kill a wizard is with Winged Death.  It's the druid version of a lure.  Along the same lines, the &quot;bug&quot; series of dots will normally stick, but I find a well placed WD and a bunch of CB's on yourself is more useful.  It the wizard is half way decently equiped, you won't be landing any useful DD's/roots/snares/epics.<br>
<br>
